cs.DS, cs.CG, cs.IT, cs.DM, cs.CC. 

The paper deals with a data structure problem in computational geometry, specifically the problem of approximate range counting. Therefore, cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) are the most likely categories. The paper also involves information theory (cs.IT), combinatorics (cs.DM), and complexity theory (cs.CC) in proving a lower bound, making these categories also likely.
